Oh, hey.
I found this thing again. 
I knew I had one, but I couldn't figure it out...
Loving my icon at the moment. 
Oh, Mulder.
You are my little gentleman. 

I also love my teenage angsty posts. Apparently I didn't hit that stage until 19. Laughing out loud so hardcore.

i am incredibly stressed out and scared.
i am sad and i don't know why.
i want to move to a beautiful island in the middle of the pacific where i don't have to do a damn thing except lay in the sun.

Yeah, I'm pretty sure I haven't written in here for a good two months. But now I'm bored, so I'll update. The week from hell is over--last midterm this morning which means that my spring break officially starts now. Debating whether or not I really want to go to work. I hate the middle school, and I'm so tired that I might fall asleep on my laptop. But, I need to save my money for Australia. Yep, I'm going abroad. Or hoping that I'm going. I don't really know if I'm going, but I want to go. Minus the plane ride--I hate planes. And with my luck, it'll crash. 

But enough about all that gloriousness. I'm looking forward to getting trizzashed tonight. Megan and I both don't have any classes tomorrow so we're going to play "drink the beer" a la "Family Guy." Pretty sure we'll win every time, and I'm hoping that I get the high score. :)

I can't hear out of my right ear very well. I don't think that's a good thing. Eh, oh well. 


Back to Aberdeen tomorrow. Yay. Or not. No one's going to be home. Hopefully, I'll be down in Towson for most of the time seein' my girls...I miss you guys. 

Okay, I'm not going to work. I'm going to sleep. and then I'm going to the lax game, because I'm cool. Check ya later.
I'm tired. I'm lonely. I'm in a rut. I want out.

I honestly don't know what to say right now. I knew you, but not as well as most others. I remember the first time I met you--you took me and Robby to Subway. You didn't even know me, and yet you were so friendly, so warm and so hysterically funny. You were the actress, the musician, the brain, the everything. I know you loved New York. I remember you talking about it all the time. You were going somewhere. You knew what you wanted in life, and you went for it all the way. I always wished that I had known you better than I did. You made everyone laugh so much. Mike, Rose, Sarah, Jen, Ginna...all of them. And now I'll never get that chance. Never.


I realize how fragile life really is. One minute you're here, and the next, you're not. It's not something that you can control. You need to really cherish what you have, because it won't be here forever. I can't imagine losing another friend, but I know that I will. I just want you all to know how much you mean to me. You have saved me time and time again. You are the hands that pick me up when I fall down, the voices that make me laugh. You are all so wonderful.

I just spent a good 2 hours going through all kinds of random crap in my room. All my old papers, notebooks, pictures, Christmas and birthday cards...everything. I can't believe that I keep all of that shit, but I do. I found some cards from Ed, and almost started crying. Did I love him? Maybe. He was such a great guy. I'm an idiot for letting him go. I really am.

I found a card from my friend Kimm from my graduation...

"I hope you will always be guided by those who love you most.
And remember, home is where the heart is.
You will always be in my heart."

There were all kinds of pictures and notes from middle and high school. It feels like so long ago. I was laughing when I read some of the stuff that Josh Bolich and I used to write to each other during our classes senior year. I miss him. I really do. I miss everyone. I miss that year. I was so happy.

I guess it's just time to let go and realize that nothing lasts forever. I know who my friends are, and I know who will be there for me when I need them. They always have been. I just wasn't always aware of it.

yeah, i'm bored. i should be doing something productive, but i'm not. maybe i should be in bed, but i'm not. i suck at life. kthanksbye.

i'm stressed out. 
stressed isn't the word for it.
there is no word for it.
i'm going to fail out of college. 
kelly and i just discovered that we must take 25 classes to complete our majors and the secondary ed requirement:

- both intro history courses (4 classes)
- 8 upper level history courses (to complete the major)
- macro, poli sci, world geography and anthro (4 classes--all for the social studies certification)
- and 9 ed classes. 
- 4+8+4+9=25

mind you, a major is usually 8 classes.
ouch.
and i still have to finish all of my gen ed requirements. 
oh god. 
the children in the middle school were getting on my nerves today.
so was the teacher. she made me grade a shitload of papers and organize random crap for her.
am i her bitch?
probably. 
i have slept 6 out of 54 hours.
this can't be good. 
and you're an asshole. 
you probably don't know who i'm talking about.
but you are. 
ihateyoubuticantstopthinkingaboutyou.
but i'm going away this weekend, and having a lot of fun. 
okay, i'm going to be late to class. again. 
goodbye.





sorryineededtoventthisshitoutkthanksbye.
oh yeah--i've just realized that i am quite possibly the WORST paper writer ever. i dont' know how i got into college. god, that just made me really depressed. ugh.

Yeah, so as you can guess, I suck at updating. What's new, what's new...had an awesome weekend or two. Beach Bash on Friday--it was grand. Lots of drunken fun. Katie and I were drunk at 3:00 in the afternoon. We went and picked up her computer from OIT, and I decided that it would be fun to steal the little "please ring bell for service" bell...so I did. Klepto much? Eh, you all know how I am. Saturday night there was an orange fence party in the quad--so basically, as long as you were within the boundaries of the fence, you could drink and do whatever. It was grand. I was wasted. The roomie and I took a long walk and talk afterwards, and then we mealed on some leftover chinese food at 3am. Haha, always a fun time. 

As for this week, there is only one phrase that can describe it: it's going to rape me up the ass without vaseline, and all I can do is bend over, grab my ankles, and smile. I had a massive anxiety attack last night. It sucked. Today was one exam and one paper. Okay, seriously, who writes an essay question like this: "There are reasons why colonization began around 1500. Discuss." I busted up laughing at that...all I could think of was Linda Richman on Coffee Talk...WOO SNL! But yeah, I'm pretty sure I fucked it up hardcore. 

God, I'm so inarticulate. I wrote a paper yesterday, and I just couldn't get my point across. Not to mention the essay exams. And the fact that I can't read out loud--that's a lost cause. Yeah, I'm going to make a great teacher. What happened to me being smart? I know that I was at one point.

...and then I found alcohol. 


I went to bed at 5:45 last night, and got up somewhere around 7:45...maybe that explains the total lack of any sort of organization to this entry. And substance. 


I'm rollin'. Peace.

I forgot to add that Katie and I went on a destructive spree tonight. 

-duct taped, tp'd and lotioned these bitches door. they better learn to yell "flush" from now on...
-stole some dining hall chairs
-and there may or may not be a plant missing from the cove. did we have something to do with this? .....perhaps.




yeah, i just realized that i'm definitely still drunk. typing is kinda hard.

I was going to go with Megan down to her friend's house down on Queen Street, but her friends ended up being ready to leave before we got there, so we just stayed in Kent. Drank with Lynn, Katie, and random other people. Always a lot of fun. I don't know what I'd do without these girls. Most amazing people ever. Headed over to Middle at around 12, but didn't stay too long. PS was outside when we left. Asses. Anyway, currently just hanging around the room with the roomie. Love it. I'm so tired, but I don't feel like climbing the ladder up to my bed. Too far. Yeah.

It's been a while. Let's recap:

Went to Canada. It was a bangin' good time. God bless being legal to drink. And the exchange rate. Came back to wac on Saturday. Had an amazing time on Saturday night for the most part. Note to all: never drink a bottle of champagne and then beer. THE BUBBLES! THE BUBBLES! ...they'll get ya in the end. Class started on Monday. I actually think I'm going to enjoy it this semester. My medieval history teacher is awesome, and I think I'm going to enjoy my acting class. Maybe it will make me more confident....or not. Currently, I'm sitting at my computer, waiting for m y laundry to finish so that I can throw it in the dryer. I really, desperately need a nap. Class at 4, and I haven't started reading. Will I? Who knows. Anywho, see ya'll later.

So I highlighted my hair today. It was supposed to come out golden brown/blondish, and some of it did. The rest is sort of an auburn/reddish color. It's...interesting...but growing on me a little. Last day of work tomorrow! WOOOOHOOOOO! So excited! Then Canada on Sunday! Yay for shopping with the grandparents, late nights at the bars, and days at the lake! Hopefully I'll be able to fit everything in. After that, it's a mad dash to get packed, and I head down to WAC! Kent 205, baby. It's gonna be great.

...kent only has 2 floors, so there is no kent 300. hahaha megan, i still love you though!


Okay, I'm thinking that I'm going to chill out with some ice cream and tv. Sounds like a plan. See ya'll!

ahahaha yesterday was awesome. it's so nice to have 3 days off in a row. let's recap, shall we? 

Sunday: spent most of the day in my pajamas, watching comedy central. i love stand up. i was dying. proceeded to actually get dressed, then went to bel air to shop with lindsey. got a sweet new purse, and some stuff for school. and chinese food, of course. 

Monday: refused to get out of bed until 12. laid by the pool for an hour, then quickly got dressed and ran up to bel air to pick up my shoes from linds. woo new shoes! stopped by target to see mike...and pick up coffee creamer. mike told me that he might have an extra ticket to the o's game that night...holla! went home, ran, lifted, then drove up to aberdeen to drop off debbie's hockey book. mike called, and i rushed home to quickly wash my hair (yeah, i definitely haven't showered since like late saturday night...), and sped down to towson. it was a fun time, full of drunks shouting things. BAD CALL! THAT WAS A BAD CALL! 

Today: couldn't get to sleep until after 4 (damn the olympics...it sucks me in!). woke up late, tried to make hard boiled eggs...did not succeed. gave up on breakfast, and now i'm in the basement getting ready to do a little lifting, then taking a shower, and maybe getting my hair highlighted. we'll see what happens. 


it's hard to believe we go back to school in 12 days. wow. i leave for canada on sunday. my aunt denise is going to be there, which is nice, because i haven't seen her in like 5 years. yeah, that sounds about right. i'm going to talk to her about going out to visit in california sometime. wooo. anywho, i better start doing some things around here. see ya.

...it's been a while since i last updated. not much has happened. class is over, but i think i already mentioned that. work sucks, but that's normal. went shopping yesterday...bought some notebooks and stuff like that. can't believe we're going back in 17 days! i'm excited :o) i leave for canada next sunday, and i can't wait to go to clifton hills with lindsey! it's going to be a blast! what else...i have to give the other lindsey some money so that i can get my shoes...2 pairs of shoes (some hot vans and new balance) for $65? yeah, it definitely pays to have a friend who works at a shoe store. reallllly does. bought a new cd the other day--the killers. i really like it. it reminds me of something from the 80's. and, it was only 9 bucks. i'm thrifty and loving it! well, gotta work at 5:45 tomorrow morning, so goodnight!

 "If you want me to wear 37 pieces of flair like your pretty boy over there Brian, why don't you just make the minimum 37 pieces of flair?"

so yes, very uninteresting night. i ended up taking my little cousin to see that hilary duff movie...it was 1 1/2 hours of pure torture, although chad michael murray isn't too bad to look at. he's not really my type, though. i like dark-haired guys over blondes. but caitlin loved it, and that's what counts, although i think she was mad that i didnt buy any popcorn (i'm cheap--what can i say?)

So the exhaust pipe fell off my car today. I had no idea what was going on--I stopped to get gas at this really sketched out Exxon station (cuz I had my mom's speedpass by accident, and why not fill 'er up?) and as soon as I got on 295, my car sounded like a plane taking off. I was just about ready to go back to the gas station and start screaming at them for having water in my tank, but I decided to just drive home. Thank god I didn't break down in the tunnel. Anyway, got home and my dad checked it out...and I have no exhaust pipe. So yeah, that was fun. 

The last couple days have been a blur of work and class, class and work. It stormed hardcore on Tuesday and Wednesday. I almost got stuck on Shucks road--it was all flooded and I had to turn around about a quarter of the way down. So I'm flashing my high-beams at people headed that way to warn them, and most turned around except this one jackass in a little red sports car who proceeded to speed up, hit the 4 inches of water I was in, hydroplane and almost knock me into/over the guardrail. I really really hope he got stuck somewhere. Goddamn mid-life crisis bald assholes. 

Yesterday, Rachel and I FINALLY found some time to get together for dinner. I miss her. We've both been so busy. Everyone has been so busy. It's crazy! I still haven't seen Kyle, and I've only seen Lindsey a few times. It's crrrrrazy! 

I continue to hate my job with a passion. It really makes me want to die inside, and I'm not kidding. Today was no exception, but yesterday was worse. Something about customers and having to be polite all the time...sometimes I just want to tell someone to get their head out of their ass and go fuck themselves. However, I would lose my job and my income, so that's not happening any time soon. 

Okay, it's time for sleep, which is pretty pathetic considering it's only 11:30. But, I promised my little cousin I would take her to go get her ears pierced tomorrow. Shit, I'm not sure if I can do it. Doesn't she need a guardian? We'll figure it out. 

Goodnight, all.



and on a random sidenote, I just saw a hot picture of Johnny Depp and nearly creamed my panties. something about him just does it for me. hahhaa. i need a boyfriend.
Ed is going to Iraq. I think I'm going to cry. If anything happens to him...

Who do you have to FUCK in this town to get a hot dog?

 

 

 

this sums up my views on life. have a wonderful night.

It's been a fun few days. Some of my family came down from Canada for the weekend because my 3 little cousins were finally getting baptized. Friday night, my parents weren't around so they let me have some wine. Well, a lot of wine. I think the point was to get me drunk, but it didn't quite work out that way. My two aunts, however, were pretty hammered. It was hysterically funny. Aunt Patty just kept telling me that my mom was fun. "Your mom, she's a fun person. She's just really fun. Really fun woman. She's so fun." ...it went on like that for a few minutes. 

Saturday was work, and then Alex, Matt, Natalie and I went to see "Anchorman"...which I loved by the way. It reminded me of Goulet in a way...Joy, you'll have to see this and let me know if I'm totally wrong with that comment. 

Yesterday were the baptisms. Uncle Jim came down to do them--the archbishop himself. It's sad that I'm related to someone so high up in the church. Anyway, I've never been to a baptism so funny. I'm Aiden's godmother now, which will be great fun. 

As for today, I'm not sure what I'm going to do. I'm contemplating going downstairs to go back to sleep for a while. Actually, I have class tonight, which sucks. Maybe I'll go see Lindsey.
